      "note": "Regarding my occasional rendering of idh (at the beginning of a sentence) as \"lo\", see surah 2, note 21. In the above context, this interjection connects with the preceding passage, which states, by implication, that the apostles are not responsible for the reactions of those to whom they communicate the divine message: a connection that is brought out fully in verses 116-117 below."
